gies.md:353:   [`strategies/predefined_strategies.json`](../strategies/predefined_strategies.json)\n./forge/README.md:92:Strategies are declared in `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Prompt text\n./forge/benchmarks/benchmark_runner.py:28:STRATEGIES_PATH = Path(os.path.join(REPO_ROOT, \"strategies\", \"predefined_strategies.json\"))\n./forge/benchmarks/benchmark_runner.py:39:        description=\"Run a benchmark suite of libraries using a predefined strategy and aggregate results.\",\n./forge/prompt_templates/persistent/default_agent_rules.md:6:- Never generate, write, or modify reachability metadata or Native Image config entries. Do not create or edit `reachability-metadata.json`, `reflect-config.json`, `resource-config.json`, `proxy-config.json`, `serialization-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, `predefined-classes-config.json`, or any other file under `src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image`; Forge handles metadata generation and merging externally.\n./forge/prompt_templates/persistent/dynamic_access_rules.md:17:- Never generate, write, or modify reachability metadata or Native Image config entries. Do not create or edit `reachability-metadata.json`, `reflect-config.json`, `resource-config.json`, `proxy-config.json`, `serialization-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, `predefined-classes-config.json`, or any other file under `src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image`; Forge handles metadata generation and merging externally.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:77:- `--strategy-name NAME` select a predefined workflow strategy from `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Defaults to `javac_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.5`.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:122:- `--strategy-name NAME` select a predefined workflow strategy from `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Defaults to `basic_iterative_pi_gpt-5.4` (Pi agent).\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:224:- Run `ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py` for a predefined set of libraries.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:232:  - `strategy`: strategy name matching an entry in `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:268:Agents are registered via `Agent.register(...)` and selected per-strategy through the `agent` field in `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Supported agents:\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:327:    python3 utility_scripts/schema_validator.py strategy strategies/predefined_strategies.json\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:344:The project uses registry-based workflow and agent abstractions. Each workflow strategy is a Python class that inherits from `WorkflowStrategy` and is registered via a decorator. Agents are registered in the same way via `Agent.register(...)`. Strategies are configured through `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`, which defines the workflow, agent, model, optional provider, prompts, optional persistent instructions, and parameters for each strategy.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:350:If you want to run an existing workflow with a different model or tuned parameters, add a new entry to `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Reuse the same `workflow` and `agent` as the base strategy, and differentiate by appending a space and a descriptor to the name:\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:390:1. **Add a strategy entry** to `strategies/predefined_strategies.json` with the matching workflow, agent, prompts, and parameters.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:424:Dynamic-access strategies can optionally download library source code, upstream tests, and/or documentation as read-only agent context. This is configured per strategy via the `source-context-types` parameter in `predefined_strategies.json`. Available types are `main`, `test`, and `documentation`. The artifacts are downloaded from URLs in the library's `index.json` (populated by the `populateArtifactURLs` Gradle task) and extracted to `local_repositories/source_context/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/`.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:428:Multiple predefined strategies exist in `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`, each using a different source-context combination:\n./forge/AGENTS.md:35:- If the change only alters wording or agent instructions, prefer `prompt_templates/` or `strategies/predefined_strategies.json` over Python logic.\n./forge/AGENTS.md:45:- `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`: declarative workflow configuration such as strategy names, prompt files, parameters, model, and agent selection.\n./forge/ai_workflows/java_fail_workflow.py:133:            \"Strategy name from strategies/predefined_strategies.json \"\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:212:            raise ValueError(f\"Fallback strategy '{FALLBACK_STRATEGY_NAME}' not found in predefined strategies\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:125:            raise ValueError(f\"Fallback strategy '{FALLBACK_STRATEGY_NAME}' not found in predefined strategies\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py:139:        help=\"select strategy by name from strategies/predefined_strategies.json\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:101:        help=f\"Strategy name from strategies/predefined_strategies.json (default: {DEFAULT_STRATEGY_NAME})\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_fails.py:76:        help=\"Strategy name from strategies/predefined_strategies.json\",\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
